GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 1137
Short Title: Appropriation to the Lake Norman CDC. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative Helfrich.
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Appropriations, if favorable, Rules, Calendar, and Operations of the House
May 4, 2026
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO APPROPRIATE FUNDS TO THE LAKE NORMAN COMMUNITY
3 DEVELOPMENT CORPORATION FOR THE SMITHVILLE REVITALIZATION PLAN
4 AND AFFORDABLE HOUSING.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6 SECTION 1. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Lake Norman
7 Community Development Corporation (Corporation) the sum of four million dollars
8 ($4,000,000) in nonrecurring funds for the 2026-2027 fiscal year to be allocated as follows:
9 (1) Two million dollars ($2,000,000) for the implementation of the Smithville
10 Revitalization Plan, including property acquisition and development of
11 affordable homes.
12 (2) Two million dollars ($2,000,000) for the development of affordable housing
13 as deemed appropriate by the Corporation, but not to be used for the
14 Smithville Revitalization Plan.
15 SECTION 2. The Corporation may use up to fifteen percent (15%) of the funds
16 appropriated for administrative costs.
17 SECTION 3. This act becomes effective July 1, 2026.
*H1137-v-1*

